post_text:
Good morning Charger Family! Two announcements for you!

#1 - Today is our first Asynchronous Day for Instruction which means that your student will be learning flexibly from home. While your student will not be expected to log into each class at a specific time, he or she is still expected to check each of the Google Classroom pages for their classes throughout the day and complete any assignments that have been posted by their teachers!

#2 - Our school spirit wear store is only open until tomorrow, Friday September 11th! We have shirts, hoodies, hats, and more! Here is the link to order your Canton Prep school spirit wear: tiny.cc/cpspiritgear

Interested in applying to Canton Prep for the 2020-2021 school year? Call 734-335-4331 or learn more here: https://bit.ly/3jqtTqx

Today is the AP Art Studio day to turn in their work and Ms. Haapala has some words of encouragement for her students!

Well, the worst is over for AP Studio. If you don’t have exceptional work to show at this point, you have two options, but really only one option because the second option is for wimps and I don’t teach wimps.

1. Participate in an event that has been a GVSU art school tradition since the world began (Laker for a Lifetime!) called “The ultimate, all night, coffee death match”;. Basically, stay up all night and make the best artwork of your life due to a combination of pressure, camaraderie in procrastination and caffeine.

2. Give up and turn in crappy work that you find on pinterest or tumblr and recreate.

I recommend a light roast- it has more caffeine.

Today is the AP Government exam day and Mr. Fite has some words of encouragement!

AP Government students,

Today is the day! Carpe Diem! Remember to count the points and to address each verb in the FRQ! And for goodness sake, DON'T GIVE OPINIONS! You must use the historical documents and SCOTUS cases as evidence of your positions. I'll be praying for you to have clear thoughts and calm nerves as you write today. You've got this!

Thanks for being great students! :)

Mr. Fite

It was also a fun way to spread the word within the community about our incredible school.
#cantonprep #ChargeOn #ChargerPride #GoChargers #CPHSChargers

Happy Monday Chargers!

Piggy-backing off of John Krasinski's SGN network (Some Good News), we wanted to share some good news of your fellow Chargers helping the community.

Today's feature is sophomore Akyrah Jones: she made and donated over 50 face shields to a local hospital. Way to go Akryah!

We know there are many questions surrounding the availability of food services during the emergency closure period. I am writing today to share our plan for providing nutritional resources to our families during this time.

Beginning this week through the week ending Sunday, April 5, we are committed to distributing lunch meals at Canton Prep to be prepared and eaten at your home. Student households may pick up frozen lunches (with reheating instructions) from our school at designated pick up times (see below). Please know, we will provide food for weekend days on the last distribution day of the week.

Pick up times will be between 9:00 a.m. and 11:00 a.m. on Mondays and Wednesdays, while…

post_text: Good morning Charger Family. As a friendly reminder, Canton Prep will be open today Monday March 16th until 12:00pm so that students can head to their locker to get any notebooks, laptops, chargers, binders, musical instruments, medication, or any other materials from their locker that they feel they need to prepare for virtual learning at home as we continue to figure out how to move forward based on what the State tells us. We are awaiting additional guidance and will update you with information as this situation evolves. Thank you for your patience and be safe.

post_text:
Good morning Charger Family! Happy Valentine's Day! We have some big news for you! Canton Prep is going to Peru in 2021! Your student is invited to join Sra. Plascencia on a once-in-a-lifetime international travel experience with their peers during Spring 2021 to Peru!

Please come to our meeting to hear to hear all the details including the destination, itinerary, and cost of this trip as well as the official opening of enrollment!

Two meetings will be held on Tuesday, February 18. One at 4:00 PM and one at 5:00PM in Room 307. Please choose which meeting you would like to attend at your convenience as both will cover the same information. The meeting should only last about 30 minutes. There are limited spots on this tour but we would love to have you attend this meeting to learn more about this exciting opportunity!

Please visit https://rsvp.eftours.com/az8ebfs to RSVP by February 17th to confirm your spot at the meeting.

Hope to see you there!

Delianise Plascencia

post_text:
Auria Solutions
December 12, 2019 at 1:15 PM ·

Auria Southfield had a special visit from Canton Preparatory High School's FIRST Robotics Competition team yesterday! The team brought in their robot from the 2019 robotics season, which was partially sponsored by Auria and supported by volunteers including Brian Pour and Bob Mamo. With hopes of recruiting more engineering and technical volunteers to assist with the design, engineering and building of their 2020 robot, the kids showcased last year’s robot and defined what they hope to build for the new season, which kicks off in January.

post_text:
Good afternoon Charger Family! We are about a week away from the beginning of school! Hope you have had an amazing summer!

With the new school year brings new students and thus brings new opportunities to carpool! Two parents have reached out needing assistance with carpooling on a ride home just for certain days. Please read the information below and see if you can help! If you can, please feel free to leave a comment along with your email address!

#1 - A student in Ypsilanti near Geddes between N Harris and Gotfredson is looking for a carpool home on Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday

#2 - A student in Westland in the Avondale and John Hix area is looking for a carpool home on Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday.

Winner, Winner!!

Mr. Brown's Advisory class won the Field Day competition today! Mr. Brown's Advisory class can wear Free Dress for the remainder of the week!!

Any student who received Student of the Month today can also wear Free Dress for the remainder of the week!!

All other students should be in full uniform.

Dismissal tomorrow, Thursday, and Friday is at 10:50 am!

Have an AMAZING night and Happy Studying!!
